#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:3
#: fc4eca57614d42c181f085b812893fe5
msgid "Windows debugging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:6
#: 4ee5be0915894afbad03c15a0e300450
msgid ""
"Debugging Windows code can be tricky in a virtualized environment. The "
"guide below assumes Qubes 4.2 and Windows 7 or later VMs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:8
#: 6b304cfe480f407f8d79c02050b75341
msgid ""
"User-mode debugging is usually straightforward if it can be done on one "
"machine. Just duplicate your normal debugging environment in the VM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:10
#: 21bcce960bf544609ce52754b3cfdb0d
msgid ""
"Things get complicated if you need to perform kernel debugging or "
"troubleshoot problems that only manifest on system boot, user logoff or "
"similar. For that you need two Windows VMs: the *host* and the *target*. "
"The *host* will contain the debugger, your source code and private "
"symbols. The *target* will run the code being debugged. We will use "
"kernel debugging over network which is supported from Windows 7 onwards. "
"The main caveat is that Windows kernel supports only specific network "
"adapters for this, and the default one in Qubes won’t work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:13
#: eaa50dab79a544d5ba6cb4b8bf11fd52
msgid "Important note"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:16
#: c997666b381f45d2a6efffb842747da4
msgid ""
"Do not install Xen network PV drivers in the target VM. Network kernel "
"debugging needs a specific type of NIC or it won’t work, the network PV "
"drivers interfere with that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:18
#: 0ff7401b58b24ce79fae0ac04fe8e5cd
msgid ""
"If you have kernel debugging active when the Xen PV drivers are being "
"installed, make sure to disable it before rebooting (``bcdedit /set debug"
" off``). You can re-enable debugging after the reboot. The OS won’t boot "
"otherwise. I’m not sure what’s the exact cause. I know that busparams for"
" the debugging NIC change when PV drivers are installed (see later), but "
"even changing that accordingly in the debug settings doesn’t help – so "
"it’s best to disable debug for this one reboot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:23
#: f4238d188cad4c69a00ad3375a63b0df
msgid "Modifying the NIC of the target VM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:26
#: 2cbbb7ef347b4b3c8a46d20328223d5a
msgid ""
"You will need to create a custom libvirt config for the target VM. See "
"`the documentation <https://dev.qubes-os.org/projects/core-"
"admin/en/latest/libvirt.html>`__ for overview of how libvirt templates "
"work in Qubes. The following assumes the target VM is named ``target-"
"vm``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:28
#: c743946dd2a5440e827eeb6cb8b41eea
msgid ""
"Edit ``/usr/share/qubes/templates/libvirt/xen.xml`` to prepare our custom"
" config to override just the NIC part of the global template:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:30
#: 66ce77a4492b4b9497f0c709499884fd
#, python-brace-format, python-format
msgid "add ``{% block network %}`` before ``{% if vm.netvm %}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:32
#: 393c897d62fa436ea088e9e02cf5a78f
#, python-brace-format, python-format
msgid "add ``{% endblock %}`` after the matching ``{% endif %}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:36
#: 296621f95deb4157836ee76fad476a8a
msgid ""
"Copy ``/usr/share/qubes/templates/libvirt/devices/net.xml`` to "
"``/etc/qubes/templates/libvirt/xen/by-name/target-vm.xml``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:38
#: ebc045d5d9bc451d9ef7a56724571fa2
msgid "Add ``<model type='e1000'/>`` to the ``<interface>`` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:40
#: d096d107de4d464e8173c3de11abf992
#, python-brace-format, python-format
msgid "Enclose everything within ``{% block network %}`` + ``{% endblock %}``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/debugging/windows-debugging.rst:42
#: 75cd1fbea6bb4c72a8bd22e32e92025c
#, python-brace-format, python-format
msgid "Add ``{% extends 'libvirt/xen.xml' %}`` at the start."
msgstr ""

